  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "Currently Envoy returns `UnAvailable` to client if a request is rate limited by the rate limited service. However if client Envoy's retry policy says  that `UnAvailable` requests need to retried, the rate limited request will be retried. And once https://github.com/envoyproxy/envoy/issues/4735, we could probably configure it to return `RESOURCE_EXHAUSTED`, But `RESOURCE_EXHAUSTED` can it self be a valid retry options for other cases.\r\nRetry of rate limited requests may not be required. There are couple of options here\r\n1. We could adjust retry policy to exclude `RESOURCE_EXHAUSTED` - but as mentioned above it may be desirable to retry requests that are returned with `RESOURCE_EXHAUSTED` for other reasons.\r\n2. When request is rate limited, Envoy sends a header `x-envoy-ratelimited` similar` to `x-envoy-overloaded` and Envoy can skip retries.\r\n\r\n",
